Uing For Loop:

public class Binary {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n=5;
        int fact=1;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            fact*=i;
  
        }
        System.out.println(fact);
    }
}
output:

120

Using Recursion:

public class Binary {

   
       
       public static int fact(int n){
           if(n==0){
               return 1;
           }
           else{
            return n*fact(n-1);
           }
       }
        public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println(fact(5));
       }
      
   }

output:

120
